article.headline: Lamar 86, Cent. Arkansas 82
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Darren Hopkins poured in 25 points Thursday night to lead Lamar to an 86-82 victory over Central Arkansas. Hopkins made 3-of-5 from 3-point range and hit 56 percent of all his field-goal attempts. Lamar (11-14, 5-6 Southland Conference) led 37-36 at the half. Brandon Chappell added 22 points for the Cardinals, while James Davis came off the bench to score 12 points and Currye Todd had 10. UCA (8-18, 2-10) was led by Durrell Nevels, who scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. Nate Bowie scored 15 points for the Bears, while Mitch Reuter added 14, Marcus Pillow had 11 and Frederick Campbell made 10.
